  "prompt": "Can I change the nominee details in Atal Pension Yojana?",
  "response": "Yes, you can change the nominee details in the Atal Pension Yojana (APY). To do this, you generally need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Obtain the Required Form**: Visit your bank branch where you have your APY account and request the nomination change form. Some banks may also provide this form online, so you can check the bank's website for an electronic version.\n\n2. **Fill Out the Form**: Complete the form with the updated nominee details, including their name, relationship with you, and any other required information.\n\n3. **Submit Necessary Documents**: You may need to attach certain documents, such as a copy of the nominee's identification proof (like their Aadhaar card or PAN card) along with the form.\n\n4. **Submit the Form**: Return the completed form and any supporting documents to the bank branch where your APY account is held. It may be necessary to submit these in person.\n\n5. **Confirmation**: Once your details have been processed, the bank will provide confirmation of the change. This may take some time, so follow up as needed to ensure the changes have been recorded correctly.\n\nKeep in mind that procedures might vary slightly between banks, so checking directly with your bank for any specific requirements or steps is always a good idea.",
